    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the leek is cooking, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in 650ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p><p>Once the leek is soft, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1678294440431-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
