            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1678294463731-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 13 min, add the <strong>sliced carrot</strong> and <strong>browned meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 12-15 min further or until the spelt is tender and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>spring lamb meatball & spelt stew</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>mint sauce </strong>to a small bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a small splash of <strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>minty drizzle</strong></p><p>Discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
